NAME 
  lnano - Lua nano or Like nano. A slightly less primitive file editor.
SYNOPSIS
  lnano 
  lnano FILE
DESCRIPTION
  A file editor based upon GNU/Nano. Provides most or all features needed for programming such as copy/paste , syntax highlighting , , find , etc.
OPTIONS
  -h 
    Equivalent to running man lnano and displays this message.
  -v
    Show the current version and exit.
  -r 
    Opens file as read only.
  -b
    When saving a file, back up the previous version of it to the current filename suffixed with a ~.
  -c=dir
    Set the directory where nano puts unique backup files if file backups are enabled.